1/ The "Tool Trap" Protocol.

New devs think shipping volume = skill. As @DailyBaileyB said: "The shortcut becomes the limitation."

If AI writes 100% of the code, AI owns 100% of the competence. You're a spectator.

Understanding > Output. 🧠

2/ The Logic of Competence.

Copy-Pasting AI Code: High Output, Zero Retention (can't fix AI bugs).

Debugging & Refactoring: Slow Output, High Mastery (you own the logic).

One builds a portfolio. The other builds a career. 🏗️ > 🏚️

3/ The Mindset Shift

❌ Old Way: "I used AI to build a clone in 2 hours." (You're an operator).
✅ New Way: "I used AI to explain complex patterns & challenge my architecture." (You're an engineer).

Don't let the tool become your ceiling.

4/ Let's see who is actually in the arena.

Drop a link to your [Project/Build] below. Tell me specifically what problem it solves.

I'll check out every single one. 👇
